{
  "analysis": "QEMU is running with PID 1167. The monitor socket exists at /tmp/qemu-monitor.sock. VNC is listening on port 5901. Now I need to set up the web interface using noVNC/websockify and nginx on port 80.",
  "plan": "1. Check QEMU log for any issues. 2. Start websockify to bridge VNC port 5901 to a websocket port (e.g., 6080). 3. Configure nginx to serve noVNC and proxy to websockify on port 80. 4. Wait for Windows 3.11 to boot to desktop.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat /tmp/qemu.log\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "ls /usr/share/novnc/\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "nohup websockify --web /usr/share/novnc 6080 localhost:5901 > /tmp/websockify.log 2>&1 &\necho \"websockify PID: $!\"\n",
      "duration": 2.0
    }
  ],
  "task_complete": false
}

{
  "analysis": "QEMU is running, websockify is running on port 6080 bridging to VNC on 5901. noVNC files are at /usr/share/novnc/. Now I need to configure nginx to serve noVNC on port 80, proxying websocket connections to websockify on 6080.",
  "plan": "Configure nginx to serve on port 80, proxying to websockify on 6080 for both HTTP and WebSocket traffic. Then verify everything works and wait for the VM to boot to the Windows 3.11 desktop.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "sleep 1 && cat /tmp/websockify.log\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat > /etc/nginx/sites-available/novnc << 'EOF'\nserver {\n    listen 80 default_server;\n    server_name _;\n\n    location / {\n        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:6080;\n        proxy_http_version 1.1;\n        proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;\n        proxy_set_header Connection \"upgrade\";\n        proxy_set_header Host $host;\n        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;\n        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;\n        proxy_read_timeout 86400;\n    }\n}\nEOF\n",
